text: California’s new coronavirus stay-at-home order will temporarily shut down outdoor dining in the state. But experts aren’t sure the ban is backed by solid data. https://t.co/bQbplFDXDF

text: The number of patients with COVID-19 currently in San Francisco hospitals is 117, a record high for the city, said Bob Wachter, the Chair of the UCSF Department of Medicine. https://t.co/Pq8W7PRasb
